✅ 1) Git - Source Control Management (VERY IMPORTANT)

Q1. What is Git?

✅ Answer : Git is a Distributed Version Control System (DVCS) used to track code changes and collaborate with teams.

📌 Why Git?
track history
rollback changes
teamwork without conflict
branching \& merging


Q2. What is Version Control System (VCS)?

✅ Answer : A system that manages file changes over time, so we can:
see history
restore old versions
work together


Q3. VCS vs CVCS vs DVCS (Common QC)

✅ Answer (Winning):

CVCS		DVCS
Central server	No single central server
Needs internet	Works offline
Example: SVN	Example: Git

📌 Why DVCS better?
works offline
faster
safe backup in each system

