✅ 4) Git Branching and Merging (HIGH SCORING)

Q12. What is a branch?

✅ Answer : A branch is an independent line of development used to work on features without affecting main code.

Q13. Create and switch branch

git branch feature-login
git checkout feature-login

Shortcut:
git checkout -b feature-login

Q14. Merge branch

git checkout main
git merge feature-login

Q15. Delete branch
git branch -d feature-login

⭐ Interview Answer

✅ git checkout is older and multi-purpose (branches + files).
✅ git switch is newer and only for switching branches, easier and safer.


Q16. What is merge conflict?

✅ Answer : Merge conflict happens when Git cannot automatically merge changes because same lines were modified in different branches.
📌 How to resolve?
open conflict file
fix code manually
add + commit

